address: 122 Streatham High Rd, London SW16 1BW, United Kingdom
name: Allison Brown
responseFromOwnerText:
Dear Allison,
We're deeply saddened to hear about your disappointment. We appreciate your feedback and are committed to making improvements. Your comments will be taken seriously as we strive to regain your trust and restore the quality you once loved.

We hope you'll give us another chance to provide you with the excellent service and quality food that we are known for.
Best Regards
La Casita
Sandra.
text:
I have been visiting La Casita for a number of years & have never been disappointed ; tonight (11/04) was the exception. The starters of cheese fries & chilli jam, calamari & garlic prawns were a mixed level of tastiness - the best were the prawns (lots of garlic butter which was great), the worst were the calamari (these were inedible & returned). The waiter did apologise & removed this item from the bill. We did order some pão caseiro bread (traditional Portuguese bread) after the starters were served - this was definitely NOT pão caseiro - very disappointing. The mains consisted of mixed fish skewer (espetada), baked salted cod (bacalhau ) & sirloin steak - all 3 were below par. The steak was NOT sirloin, it was a largish flat piece of beef with a fair amount of “flobby” fat smothered with peppercorn sauce. Half of the steak was edible & the fries & side salad were good. The bacalhau was overcooked, way too firm not soft & silky & dry to taste ; the accompanying vegetables were good. The worse was the espetada ; the tuna was hard & grey in colour, the calamari was the same as the starter, difficult to cut & “rubbery”, the prawns were near on impossible to peel as they were stuck to the shell, the salmon was hard & dry. Along with the vegetables, the whole skewer was burnt / extremely charred. Around 75% of the food was left on our plates. The waiter did ask if everything was ok when clearing our table, we did respond giving an overall opinion that everything was overcooked. Not too much conversation between us, he acknowledged & left. The bill didn’t reflect any other discount apart from the calamari starter.
Maybe an “off” night for the Chef but @ our detriment & £££ ; not good. No one goes out to have a bad / unsatisfactory meal but this was probably one of the worst meals we’ve had in a long time. NB the photo’s can & are deceiving - the food looks good but tasted the complete opposite.
title: La Casita

Our waiter was very charming. Dishes are simple and basic (in a good way) and of excellent quality and nicely prepared & served. Portion size is generous. The consensus was that everything ordered was absolutely delicious. Will definitely be back soon and delighted to recommend. Muito obrigado La Casita!

text:
I recently met up with a friend for a birthday lunch, and we had a delightful experience at this charming restaurant. The ambiance was lovely, with crisp white tablecloths and napkins that set a refined tone. The waiting staff were incredibly attentive and patient, ensuring we felt well cared for throughout our meal.

The owner was especially accommodating, which added a personal touch to our dining experience. Despite the restaurant being busy on a Sunday afternoon, it was not overcrowded, allowing us to enjoy a relaxed and pleasant chat without feeling rushed.

Overall, it was a wonderful place to celebrate a special occasion, and I highly recommend it for anyone looking for a welcoming atmosphere with excellent service.

address: 122 Streatham High Rd, London SW16 1BW, United Kingdom
name: Victoria Brown
responseFromOwnerText: Dear Victoria, Thank you for taking the time to share your experience. We're sorry to hear that your recent visit wasn't up to your expectations. We take all feedback seriously, and we appreciate your honest feedback.
text:
I had a very bizarre and odd experience at this restaurant. The atmosphere was empty and cold, with sterile and basic décor. Despite my sister's praises about the food being well-priced, I found it to be average at best. The prawn starter was basic and the corn-fed chicken with chips was nothing to write home about. The seasoning was sharp and left a strange sensation in my mouth.

However, the saving grace of the night was our waitress, Bruna. She was friendly, attentive, and truly the life of the restaurant. Despite the lack of customers, she made us feel welcome and took great care of us. We ended up staying longer than planned, enjoying multiple jugs of sangria and other drinks.

To my shock and disappointment, I later found out that Bruna had been fired for "talking too much." This decision seemed unjust and heartless, especially considering she was the only staff member who seemed to care about the guests. The restaurant lacked any music or atmosphere, making it a depressing place to dine.

I can't help but feel that there were racist undertones at play here, as the restaurant seemed to be trying to cater to a specific audience. Treating a young, hardworking employee like Bruna in such a manner is unacceptable. It's clear that this establishment is not a fine dining restaurant, even though they are obviously straining to be and I am horrified by the way they treated someone who went above and beyond to make our night enjoyable. Shame on them for ruining what could have been a pleasant experience and be warned they obviously have no respect or care about their staff.
title: La Casita

address: 122 Streatham High Rd, London SW16 1BW, United Kingdom
name: Shane Munro
text:
Had ordered from La Casita quite often during the pandemic and found their food to be absolutely delicious.

However, my partner and I had recently ordered again and we were really disappointed with what we had recieved (poor quality food and small portion sizes). I had subsequently left a bad review expressing my disappointment.

The restaurant reached out to me directly offering to redo the order. Having recieved this, I can say the portion size was a lot better and what we would expect.

My only concern is I do think the quality of the food on this occasion was not as good compared to our previous orders. Mainly the meat which was average. Perhaps a personal preference but I did have quite a bit of fat in my meat which wasn't great and my partner's steak still thin and lacked flavour. For the food I would probably go at 3.5 out of 5 (previously a 5* during pandemic).

However, overall, I will leave the restaurant with 4 stars as their customer service was outstanding and they did look to rectify where they went wrong last time to the point that they even went out their way to deliver to me themselves. They seemed very sorry for what had happened to our previous order and I accept their apology.

My only advice to the restaurant is to please keep an eye on quality control with the meat that's being sourced and how it's being cooked as I'm pretty sure there's been a negative change here compared to when we ordered back in 2020/21 (perhaps new staff? Change of supplier?).
title: La Casita

responseFromOwnerText:
We sincerely apologize that our service was not satisfactory for you. We aim to provide the most excellent customer service and carry our business with high standards. It is of deep concern that our standards were not met in your customer experience. Your satisfaction is important to us, and we will ensure this does not happen again.
We will investigate this issue and get back to you shortly. You can always contact our restaurant, 02086646033 to sort this issue even quicker.
Kind regards
text:
I'm big fan of Italian food I did eat Italian in tons other restaurants, I do cook Italian food myself very often either, and this situation I need to be honest in here.

First impression - food container too small (ok this was advertised there do small plates), then I opened the smallest one as it was a starter Garlic Mushrooms. There is not much to talk about this as its overpriced £7. Taste ok. Would rate 3 of 5.

Next my main which is, Lasagna - I believe the chief is aware of that Lasagna represents Italian culture and the opinion about restaurant vary on the pasta taste.
Well here is surprise... no, not happy surprised.
The signature dish was overcooked,  but cuoco... this godamn cuoco should learn how to cook! I dont believe he is Italian...
ITS TASTELESS and pasta overcooked.

I wasn't inside, as I ordered online, but I will never ever recommend this restaurant after what I received in delivery.

Small plates + big prices + tasteless

You need to work on this balance. If you do small plates + big prices the taste should be OUTSTANDING.
If you can't achieve this taste but want to keep prices, increase portions!
but if you dont care about taste and still want to maintain small plates, LOWER the COSTS, because this is ridiculous.

kind regards

text: Sangria eccellente con pezzi di frutta fresca. Starter Calamari fritti altrettanto gustosi accompagnati da una salsa delicata e leggermente piccante. Paella di pesce non perfetta, troppo zafferano, piena di pesce come calamari, gamberetti, cozze e gamberoni. Prezzo troppo elevato soprattutto per la sangria classica formato "Giant". Servizio veloce ma era un giovedì non busy. Locale piccolo ma accogliente con colori che richiamano la Spagna.
textTranslated: Excellent sangria with pieces of fresh fruit. Starter Fried calamari equally tasty accompanied by a delicate and slightly spicy sauce. Seafood paella not perfect, too much saffron, full of fish like calamari, prawns, mussels and prawns. Price too high especially for the classic "Giant" format sangria. Fast service but it was a not busy Thursday. Small but welcoming place with colors that recall Spain.

address: 122 Streatham High Rd, London SW16 1BW, United Kingdom
name: Annalisa Parisi
text: Io e il mio fidanzato avevamo deciso di trascorrere la sera del nostro anniversario in questo ristorante. Abbiamo aspettato più di mezz'ora per la paella che non è mai arrivata perché il cameriere ha sbagliato l'ordine e quando abbiamo chiesto spiegazioni all'altra cameriera lei ci ha risposto malissimo dicendo solo che può succedere un errore. Maleducata e assolutamente non professionale ci siamo rimasti malissimo e abbiamo chiesto il conto. Nel conto era compresa la paella che non abbiamo mangiato e il vino che non avevamo bevuto!! Non abbiamo ricevuto nemmeno delle scuse e scioccati ce ne siamo andati abbastanza delusi e scontenti. Non lo consiglio proprio! Se potessi dare 0 stelle lo farei!
textTranslated: My fiancé and I decided to spend our anniversary evening in this restaurant. We waited more than half an hour for the paella which never arrived because the waiter got the order wrong and when we asked the other waitress for explanations she replied very badly, only saying that a mistake can happen. Rude and absolutely unprofessional we were very upset and asked for the bill. The bill included the paella that we didn't eat and the wine that we didn't drink!! We didn't even receive an apology and in shock we left quite disappointed and unhappy. I really don't recommend it! If I could give 0 stars I would!
title: La Casita

Hello dear I am so sorry that you did not like the experience at our restaurant. We always try our best to give the best service and the best food possible. As a small business we work really hard on this points to make sure that our customers are happy and comes back to our restaurant. I hope you come back again and give us the chance to show you that we can provide a good service and a very tasteful food.
Many thanks
text: Terrible service and food was the worst. Seasoning was left in Spain and the seafood was obviously old and frozen (e.g. white prawns), not impressed as Paella should be their speciality and fresh food should be a must. Staff lack common sense as well as courtesy which added to the bad experience and black pepper in my pineapple juice. I cannot  recommend  this restaurant  as the food and service was not worth my hard earned  money. We waited from 8:30pm until 10 pm for our food  to be served, begged for bread and olives to prevent eating each other which were on the bill so even though we were a party of about 18 and food was so late it was not complimentary. Some of our party had to wait over 20 minutes to be seated.
